name: Celebrating Women's History Month #02
description:
The image, "Celebrating Women's History Month #02" is the second of four images in the "Celebrating Women's History Month NFT Series". It was created to honor and celebrate the roles and contributions of women past and present as we look toward the future. In 1980, the week of March 8th was designated by a Presidential proclamation as "National Women’s History Week". In the proclamation, President Jimmy Carter noted "...Too often the women were unsung and sometimes their contributions went unnoticed. But the achievements, leadership, courage, strength and love of the women who built America was as vital as that of the men whose names we know so well...". In 1987, the U.S. Congress designated the month of March as “Women’s History Month".

The images in the "Celebrating Women's History Month NFT Series" were created with the assistance of artificial intelligence, VQGAN+CLIP (machine learning algorithms), and text prompts. The image may be interpreted differently through the eyes and imagination of the viewers.
